Description: Lip and neck sherd of Milesian pre- Fikellura pottery trefoil oinochoe; yellowish slip; exterior: lip glazed black with round eye and dot rosette in added white; on neck, band of stalked rosettes (three preserved) between narrow bands.
Curator's comments: For parallels regarding the decoration on the lip, see British Museum 1864,1007.149 and Cambridge Museum of Classical Archaeology NA40. Cook placed the oinochoe into his group of 'Miscellaneous Oinochoai',
Bibliographic references: CVA British Museum 8 / Corpus Vasorum Antiquorum: Great Britain 13, British Museum 8 (p. 9, no. 1, pl. 9, no. 1)
Walter-Karydi 1973 / Samische Gefässe des 6. Jahrhunderts vor Christi: Landschaftsstile ostgriechischer Gefässe (p. 115, no. 23)
Möller 2000 / Naukratis, Trade in Archaic Greece (p. 248, no. 4)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GF.136)
